verbose_text: Inhibition of either the NF - kappaB complex or JAK-STAT4 axis blocked the polarizing activity of R848, IFNgamma, and IL-6 plus TNFalpha by 55-90%, consistent with the conclusion that these pathways are essential for the generation of MAC inflam from mMDSC.
